President Obama spoke with Chancellor Merkel of Germany and President Hollande of France to discuss the crisis in Ukraine. They expressed support for President Poroshenko's ceasefire announcement and urged Russia to withdraw its military forces from Ukraine's border, stop the flow of weapons and militants across the border, and encourage armed separatists to lay down their weapons. They agreed that if Russia does not take immediate steps to deescalate the situation, the United States and the European Union will coordinate additional measures to impose costs on Russia. They also discussed the situation in Iraq and the threat posed by ISIL.